metadata.name: tratti #33
metadata.description:
"tratti" is an Italian word that has many different meanings. When we started working on this piece, we wanted to create something that combines our traits ("tratti" in Italian).
We had this urge to channel the turbulent times we're living in now into this artwork using just lines ("tratti" in Italian).

We don't know what to do now, we're here, and that's all that matters. We're here for our families, our friends, and our community. Like everything in life, there are joyful times and challenging times. We must accept happiness as something that is not constant but that we feel at times (a "tratti" in Italian).

With "tratti", we want to send a message to every disheartened human being: "Stay strong and never let anyone or anything crush the hope in you. Joyful times are around the corner".

metadata.name: Celestial Objects #41
metadata.description:
Celestial Objects is a generative collection imagining planets and stars in the space, with light and shadows being key themes. 

The artwork is primarily rendered using hundreds of thousands of points (more than a million in some cases) to create different aspects of the output including the sky textures, shooting stars and shadows on the planets. 

Celestial Objects is coded in p5.js, and please note that it takes 5-15 seconds for each output to render.

Controls (in live view): 
Press [2] to render 2000x2000px image
Press [4] to render 4000x4000px image
Press [s] to save the current view (default window size or 2000px or 4000px image)

metadata.name: the Simurgh #87
metadata.description:
Simurgh is inherently benevolent and unambiguously female. Being a part mammal, she suckles her young. The Simurgh has teeth. It has enmity toward snakes, and its natural habitat is a place with plenty of water. Its feathers are said to be copper-colored, and though it was initially described as a dog-bird, it was later shown with either the head of a man or a dog.

Iranian legends consider the bird so old that it had seen the world's destruction three times over. The Simurgh learned so much by living so long that it is thought to possess the knowledge of all the ages. In one legend, the Simurgh was said to live 1,700 years before plunging itself into flames (much like the phoenix).
The Simurgh was considered to purify the land and waters and bestow fertility. The creature represented the union between the Earth and the sky, serving as a mediator and messenger between the two. The Simurgh roosted in Gaokerena, the HÅm (Avestan: Haoma) Tree of Life, stands in the middle of the world sea (Vourukasha). 
Simorgh was the inspiration for making this work.
Everything is generated by code written in P5js.

metadata.name: Mythic Latent Glitches  #195
metadata.description:
What is even real and what is artificial?

In the contemporary light, the division between real and artificial loses weight as the concepts become more and more intertwined. In this work, the artist combines the human and generative inputs, in a counterintuitive manner, by allowing AI to design the organic elements and using the human hand to incorporate artificial glitches. What seemingly emerges as natural forms, was imagined solely by GAN, seeing the world through the limited examples through the photographerâ€™s lenses. Artistâ€™s role is also reversed, as their goal is to design the visual destruction process of the organic forms. Glitch is a malfunction of perception, it symbolizes the confusion caused by not being able to comprehend. 

The human fascination with metaphysical forces spans many centuries. While Pagan mythology created gods living in deep forests and under-explored territories, nowadays we approach technology with somewhat similar awe, fascination, and fear. 

The project has been developed in multiple stages. It started with an inspiration by the Lithuanian landscape and research of the ancient myths and legends. The photography aimed at capturing the mysterious, spanning months and years of different experiences. A custom pre-trained artistâ€™s GAN model was then trained on a collection of several hundred photographs in high resolution. Selected outputs were curated by artist and included as a starting canvas for the next stage. Then, a set of stochastic manipulations were programmed to create alternative narratives through the visual destruction. Fog turns into smoke into burning radioactive forest in an unpredictable manner, guided by the random variables, their boundaries crafted by artist.  

Read more on the project website:
ivonatau.com/mythic-latent-glitches

- Use the "A" key to animate (if "Animated" feature is present).
- Press any key to stop the animation.
- Use the "S" key to export an image.

metadata.name: Annihilate This Week #252
metadata.description:

This is intended to be a gift for all collectors and the community of fx(hash) that showed so much support for the "Saturday" project, really beyond my expectations.

50% of the royalties goes to the minter, do with the piece whatever you'd like, hold it, sell or trade it, or even burn it if you really don't like it :)

metadata.name: Tesseract #175
metadata.description:
'Tesseract' is a generative collection drawing on the concept of the cube from oneirology, the interpretation of dreams. In many mythologies and fields of study, the square is considered a 'perfect shape', thus with its abstraction into three isometric dimensions, the cube is seen by some as a representation of the various aspects of the human condition.

In 'Tesseract', the ribbons flowing between the cubes represent the shared experiences that connect us all. No matter how different our lives might be, we all go through the same joys, sorrows, trials, tribulations and experience attachments of varying degrees. 

It is these experiences that bind us together and make us who we are. With these concepts in mind, viewers are invited to interpret each composition as it relates to them and their unique story, from the perspective of that which has been and that which is yet to be experienced.

Press 'S' to save a high resolution PNG at 2400 x 3396 px.

metadata.name: WTBS Logo with Friends #159
metadata.description:
Did you know that WTBS is now sixth months old? If we were Willâ€™s baby, weâ€™d be sitting up and prepping to crawl â€” the literal baby steps that precede an entire lifetime of movement. 

Play is another integral part of our development. Play teaches us to connect, laugh, share, love, and learn. It helps form our earliest friendships that mold us into who we are destined to become. Over the last six months we have had the immense pleasure of forming new relationships with some of the amazing artists that comprise of the fxhash community. 

It is the love and support of new friends Laurent Houdard, Ada Ada Ada, elsif, and Camille Roux that made our first (official) collaboration possible. Thank you so much for the idea, the vision, the art, the time, and the wrangling to make this possible. 

Each letter is imbued with the unique style of an artist, based on a framework created by Laurent. There is a small chance of receiving a piece with two of the same style, with the rarest possibility of receiving one with all four quadrants the same. 

Collect with love and the knowledge that your support means the world to us. Thank you for listening every week, and for the messages and stories that you share with us. We canâ€™t wait to continue to grow.

Thank you so much again to Laurent, Ada, elsif, and Camille. This is what community is.

metadata.name: SoulFish #173
metadata.description:
Named after the artist Wu Che-Yu, the soul fish was born in the void and crystallized from human emotions.

Fluttering silently and slowly, their bodies almost disappeared in the light of the deep sea.
The fish swims freely, and this is the happiness of the fish.
If we are not a fish, how do we know the joy of a fish?
How do we know that we do not know the joy of fish?
We will only learn about it when we come to the riverside.

Inspired by ZhuÄngzÇ: "The Debate on the Joy of Fish" c. 3rd century BC

metadata.name: Julia's Magical Bulbs - The Second Power #51
metadata.description:
Julia's Magical Bulbs are 3D dimensional fractals, based on the Julia Sets of the Mandelbulb fractal.

The token is interactive, use your mouse-wheel to zoom-in and see all the little details. You will find a menu in the lower-right corner which allows you to play with the iterations and camera position. You can also render high-resolution images here.

A little bit of magic happens when you select low iteration values, perhaps your token will even default to this. 

Technical:

Not all browsers support multi-threaded modules, the fallback mode is quite slow. Try Chrome if your browser is not supported.

Calculated in full 64-bit on the CPU (not the GPU) for more accurate and detailed images.

metadata.name: Primordial #12
metadata.description:
Primordial is a study of abstract forms. The algorithm, written in p5.js and WebGL, utilizes domain warping to create twisted fields of color and then overlays thousands of tiny lines to provide depth and texture. The outputs are chaotic but not completely formless, like a swirling mass of plasma from the early universe, or a strange proto-life form suspended in prehistoric ooze.

CONTROLS:

1-9: Increase resolution and save image in PNG format

B: Toggle borders on/off

F: Fullscreen
P: Portrait
L: Landscape
S: Square

For third party license information, please see license.md

David Brice Allen
October 2022
